This paper discusses the use of information centrality for intrusion detection in large networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need to mine large data sets, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a more efficient way to compute information centrality, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
